            "answer_text": "It\u2019s called creating a \u201ccommon tongue\u201d. Before an operation, or during a scouting mission, different targets are given different code names. A building could be \u201cmagenta\u201d a checkpoint could be called \u201calpha/ bravo/ Charlie\u201d or even \u201cValkyrie\u201d or \u201cpotato\u201d. Basically, any wack name you can think of. It really doesn\u2019t matter, as long as the main target points have code names, and everyone knows which code name refers to what target/ check- point. In my experience, people really enjoyed giving these code names, taking pride in a target named after their colloquial term. Go figure. ",
