            "answer_text": "Usually by map grid numbers. The various units have maps with a numbered grid on them, such as A-14. So the one unit tells the other unit, such as the artillery battery that the enemy is in grid A-14 of the map. The artillery unit then knows where to drop the barrage. Now with the advent of GPS and satellite locating capability they may use something else today. Map grids is the way we did it back in the day though. ",
